# Liquibase Migration Rule (Spring Boot & PostgresSQL)

When asked to create or update migrations, read all entities in `src/main/java/com/prelude/randomz/entity/` and generate Liquibase YAML changelogs based on the current Java state.
## 0. Entity Scope — Read Before Doing Anything

**Always ask the user first:**
> "Bạn muốn generate migration cho entity nào? (VD: `Player`, `Room`, `Team` hoặc `all` để gen hết)"

- If user specifies entities (e.g., `Player`, `Room`) → **only read those files**.
- If user says `all` → read all files in `src/main/java/com/prelude/randomz/entity/`, skip enums and `MetaData`.
- Do **not** scan the entity folder until scope is confirmed.

## 1. File & Path Conventions
- **Format**: YAML
- **Path**: `src/main/resources/db/changelog/changes/`
- **Naming**: `DDMMYYYY-NNN-description.yaml` (e.g., `19032026-001-create-table-player.yaml`).
- **Master Changelog**: `src/main/resources/db/changelog/master.yaml`. Always append an `include` entry for every new file created.

## 2. ChangeSet Conventions
- **Author**: `van.qui`
- **ID format**: `NNN-NN` (File sequence number + sub-sequence, e.g., `001-01`, `001-02`).
- **Fail Strategy**: Use `failOnError: true` for all structural changes (createTable, addColumn, modifyDataType).
- **Rollback**: Every `changeSet` MUST include a valid `rollback` block (e.g., `dropTable` for `createTable`, `dropColumn` for `addColumn`).

## 3. Java-to-PostgreSQL Type Mapping

| Java Type | PostgreSQL Column Type | Constraints / Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `UUID` (with `@Id`) | `uuid` | `primaryKey: true` only. No `defaultValueComputed`, no `autoIncrement`. App handles ID generation. |
| `Long` (with `@Id`) | `bigint` | `primaryKey: true` only. No `autoIncrement`. App handles ID generation. |
| `String` | `varchar(255)` | Use `@Column(length = N)` value if specified, else default 255 |
| `Long` (non-ID) | `bigint` | |
| `Integer` / `int` | `integer` | |
| `Double` / `Float` | `float8` / `float4` | |
| `BigDecimal` | `numeric(19,4)` | |
| `Instant` / `LocalDateTime` | `timestamp` | |
| `LocalDate` | `date` | |
| `Boolean` / `boolean` | `boolean` | Include `defaultValueBoolean` if field is initialized in entity |
| `UUID` (non-ID) | `uuid` | Plain column, no FK constraint inferred |
| `List<UUID>` | `uuid[]` | PostgreSQL array type, no FK constraint inferred |
| `byte[]` | `bytea` | |
| `JsonNode` / `Map` | `jsonb` | |
| Enum (`EnumType.STRING`) | `varchar(50)` | |
| Enum (`EnumType.ORDINAL`) | `integer` | ⚠️ Add comment warning: avoid ordinal enums, fragile on reorder |

## 4. Column Naming & Constraints

- **Table name**: `snake_case` of the entity class name (e.g., `Player` → `player`, `GameRoom` → `game_room`).
- **Column name**:
  - If field has `@Column(name = "custom_name")` → use `custom_name`.
  - Otherwise → convert field name to `snake_case` (e.g., `startTime` → `start_time`, `currentMode` → `current_mode`).
- **Nullable**:
  - `@Column(nullable = false)` → `constraints: { nullable: false }`.
  - No annotation → column is nullable by default, omit constraints block.
- **Unique**:
  - `@Column(unique = true)` → `constraints: { unique: true, uniqueConstraintName: "uk_{table}_{column}" }`.
- **`@Column(columnDefinition = "...")`** → use the value as-is for the column `type` field.
  - e.g., `@Column(columnDefinition = "text")` → `type: text`
  - e.g., `@Column(columnDefinition = "uuid[]")` → `type: uuid[]`
  - Ignore all other type mapping rules when `columnDefinition` is present — it takes priority.
- **`@Column(precision = P, scale = S)`** → override `BigDecimal` default to `numeric(P, S)`.
  - e.g., `precision = 10, scale = 2` → `type: numeric(10,2)`
  - If only `precision` is set without `scale` → `numeric(P, 0)`.
  - If neither is set → fallback to default `numeric(19,4)`.

## 5. Relationship & FK Rules

> ⚠️ This project does NOT use JPA relationship annotations (`@ManyToOne`, `@OneToOne`, `@ManyToMany`, `@OneToMany`).
> Relationships and foreign keys are managed **entirely via Liquibase**, not inferred from entity fields.

- **Never auto-generate FK constraints** from field names like `playerId`, `roomId`, etc.
- Fields like `UUID playerId` or `List<UUID> playerId` are plain columns (`uuid` or `uuid[]`). Treat them as data columns only.
- FK constraints and indexes are added **only when explicitly requested** by the user in a separate migration.

## 6. MetaData Columns (Inherited)

All entities extend `MetaData`. Always append these 7 columns to every `createTable`, after all entity-specific columns:

| Column | Type | Constraints |
|---|---|---|
| `created_date` | `timestamp` | |
| `updated_date` | `timestamp` | |
| `deleted_date` | `timestamp` | |
| `created_by` | `varchar(255)` | |
| `updated_by` | `varchar(255)` | |
| `deleted_by` | `varchar(255)` | |
| `is_deleted` | `boolean` | `defaultValueBoolean: false` |

## 7. Mandatory Workflow

1. **Read entities**: Scan all files in `src/main/java/com/prelude/randomz/entity/`. Ignore non-entity classes (e.g., enums, `MetaData` base class itself).
2. **Read existing changelogs**: Scan `src/main/resources/db/changelog/changes/` to understand what has already been migrated.
3. **Diff & decide**:
   - Table does not exist in any changelog → generate `createTable`.
   - Table exists but has new fields → generate `addColumn`.
   - Field type changed → generate `modifyDataType` with a ⚠️ comment warning to verify PostgreSQL casting compatibility manually.
4. **Generate YAML**: One file per logical task. Follow naming and ID conventions.
5. **Register**: Append the new file path to `master.yaml`. Ensure files are ordered by dependency (referenced tables must appear before tables that depend on them).

